<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id5fff70c5-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58" identifier="/us/usc/t30/s287"><num value="287">§ 287.</num><heading> Extension of prospecting permits</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any prospecting permit issued under this subchapter may be extended by the Secretary of the Interior for a period not exceeding two years, upon a showing of satisfactory cause.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id5fff70c6-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58">(<ref href="/us/act/1927-02-07/ch66/s7">Feb. 7, 1927, ch. 66, § 7</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/act/1932-05-07/ch174">May 7, 1932, ch. 174</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/47/151">47 Stat. 151</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id5fff70c7-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id5fff70c8-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id5fff70c9-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was not enacted as part of <ref href="/us/act/1920-02-25/ch85">act Feb. 25, 1920, ch. 85</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/41/437">41 Stat. 437</ref>, known as the Mineral Leasing Act, which comprises this chapter.</p>
</note>
</notes>
